<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Please don't think I'm disagreeing with you, because I'm not. Just throwing out another perspective is all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If it sounds like I'm snarling, you're right.  But it's not you that is making me mad, it's what Verant has done to this spawn.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I think the heart of the discussion is about morality, not rules. If folks believe that &quot;putting in the time&quot; constitutes &quot;entitlement&quot;, then we've got a bottleneck. Perhaps one big enough to constitute the need of a rotation.<br>
<br>
If folks believe that &quot;might equals right, we've got the levels, the speed, the organization, and the power&quot; constitutes &quot;entitlement&quot;, then the competition gets fierce and potentially ugly.<br>
<br>
